Patch: change Metabase's hard-coded "Metabase" defaults to "Tanuh", and
point the favicon at our overlaid logo.png so the browser tab icon is
the Tanuh logo.

Three settings live in src/metabase/appearance/settings.clj:

  - application-name: the word substituted in user-facing copy, including
    the browser tab title (rendered via {{{applicationName}}} in
    resources/frontend_client/index_template.html).

  - site-name: the instance display name shown in admin and emails.

  - application-favicon-url: the URL the HTML <link rel="icon"> resolves
    to. We point it at app/assets/img/logo.png — the Tanuh PNG that the
    Dockerfile overlays at resources/frontend_client/app/assets/img/logo.png.
    Browsers will scale it down for the tab.

application-name and application-favicon-url are :feature :whitelabel for
write access on OSS, meaning the admin UI cannot change them, but the
default value is what runs.

If this patch fails to apply on a Metabase upgrade, re-anchor against the
new content of src/metabase/appearance/settings.clj — see
reportingSystem/tanuh-metabase/BUILD_GUIDE.md "Upgrading Metabase".

diff --git a/src/metabase/appearance/settings.clj b/src/metabase/appearance/settings.clj
--- a/src/metabase/appearance/settings.clj
+++ b/src/metabase/appearance/settings.clj
@@ -17,13 +17,13 @@
   :type       :string
   :audit      :getter
   :feature    :whitelabel
-  :default    "Metabase")
+  :default    "Tanuh")

 (defsetting site-name
   (deferred-tru "The name used for this instance of {0}."
                 (setting/application-name-for-setting-descriptions application-name))
   :encryption :no
-  :default    "Metabase"
+  :default    "Tanuh"
   :audit      :getter
   :visibility :settings-manager
   :export?    true)
@@ -201,7 +201,7 @@
   :type       :string
   :audit      :getter
   :feature    :whitelabel
-  :default    "app/assets/img/favicon.ico")
+  :default    "app/assets/img/logo.png")

 (defsetting show-metabot
   (deferred-tru "Enables Metabot character on the home page")
